---
import VizPlaceholder from '../../VizPlaceholder.astro';
---

<section id="knowledge" class="px-6 py-20 md:py-28">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
    <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-accent">
      The company brain
    </p>
    <h2
      class="mt-4 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-neutral-50 sm:text-4xl"
    >
      The knowledge walks out the door
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-neutral-300">
      <p>
        Think about how this plays out at a company, because the session problem
        is really a knowledge problem. As your responsibility rises, you stop
        reading every implementation. As a system architect you care that the
        data flows through the application the right way; you do not sit at the
        keyboard of every developer shipping a feature. The developer holds those
        details. And when that developer changes jobs, the knowledge leaves with
        them, because it was almost never written down.
      </p>
      <p>
        Agents are developers who leave after every single task. The reasoning
        that went into an implementation is right there while the session runs,
        and then the session ends and the agent forgets. Session logs exist, but
        they are <mark>local to one machine, invisible to the org</mark>. The
        workaround people reach for is ADRs, architectural decision records, but
        it is a workaround: where do you store them, and how do you share them
        across an organization? The multiplayer nature of agentic work, many
        people and many agents drawing on the same accumulated understanding, is
        the part nobody has solved with a document.
      </p>
      <p class="font-medium text-neutral-100">
        A meta-harness turns sessions into shared organizational memory. The
        reasoning stops walking out the door, because it never lived behind one
        door to begin with.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mx-auto mt-14 max-w-5xl">
    <VizPlaceholder
      label="developers leaving with knowledge draining away, versus sessions feeding a shared org-wide memory that stays"
    />
  </div>
</section>
